					<description><![CDATA[<p>In a historic first for Canada’s homegrown defense technology industry, an Ottawa-based startup, Dominion Dynamics, has raised a jaw-dropping $139 million CAD (US$100 million) Series A, which, it is believed,</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/dominion-dynamics-raises-139m-cad-for-arctic-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Dominion Dynamics Raises $139M CAD for Arctic Expansion</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In a historic first for Canada’s homegrown defense technology industry, an Ottawa-based startup, </span><a href="https://defendthedominion.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Dominion Dynamics</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, has raised a jaw-dropping $139 million CAD (US$100 million) </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/leapxpert-raises-180m-to-unlock-insights-from-work-chats/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Series </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">A, which, it is believed, sets the record for the single largest Series A ever raised by a Canadian defence technology company. It marks the beginning of a fundamental transition toward sovereign, pan-track, state-of-the-art solutions to defend that large, highly contested northern frontier.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This funding round was led by an existing investor, the Toronto-based growth equity fund Georgian, and included a substantial crowd of domestic institutional and notable international defense technology investors, including Valour Equity Partners, the Valour Atreides AI Fund, Expeditions, Lakestar, OMERS Ventures, the BDC Capital’s Strong North Fund, Deloitte Ventures, Royal Bank of Canada (RBC), and JDY Capital. Founding investors Bessemer Venture Partners and the B.C. Investment Management Corporation (BCI), which funded the company earlier, also invested again.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Push for Sovereignty in the High Arctic</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The massive capital injection arrives at a critical geopolitical moment. Rising global tensions and melting polar ice have turned the Arctic into a strategic focal point, forcing Canada and its NATO allies to reconsider northern security. Historically, Canada has lagged behind peer nations in military spending and has relied heavily on the United States for continental defence. Dominion Dynamics aims to change that dynamic by building a domestic &#8220;defense neo-prime&#8221; capable of providing independent, persistent surveillance across more than 200,000 kilometres of rugged coastline.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_203252" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203252" class="size-large wp-image-203252" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Dominion-Dynamics-1024x328.jpg" alt="Dominion Dynamics" width="1024" height="328" /><p id="caption-attachment-203252" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Dominion Dynamics</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Operating in the High Arctic presents severe physical obstacles. The region suffers from extreme sub-zero temperatures, sprawling geography, and a complete lack of traditional cellular or satellite infrastructure. Dominion’s software and hardware stacks are engineered specifically to survive these inhospitable conditions, allowing the military to track and analyze data where conventional systems fail.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/leapxpert-raises-180m-to-unlock-insights-from-work-chats/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">LeapXpert Raises $180M to Unlock Insights From Work Chats</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Scaling AuraNet and the Arctic Mesh Network</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Dominion&#8217;s database foundation is AuraNet, a distributed, map-based software that integrates sensors, operators, and autonomous systems into a seamless picture of operation. AuraNet is a data fusion layer that links telemetry across a severely degraded or completely nonexistent communications infrastructure.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform has just passed an important validation trial as part of the Canadian Armed Forces&#8217; annual Operation Nanook-Nunalivut in the High Arctic. Over two months, the Canadian Rangers used Dominion&#8217;s arctic-hardened sensors and software to coordinate mission tracking, planning and real-time communication in remote terrain.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">However, the new venture capital will also allow for hardware enhancement; essentially, an increased embodiment of the software. Examples of this are an increase in the number of remote sentry towers, which offer constant surveillance of distant northern airstrips, and IceSpike, an autonomous sensor system deployed by helicopter into the face of an ice sheet, which slowly burrows through the ice to deposit acoustic sensors into sub-ice waters.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Taking a Big Swing on Autonomous Flight</span></h2>
<div>
<div data-test-render-count="1">
<div class="group">
<div class="contents">
<div class="group relative relative pb-[var(--msg-assistant-pb,0.75rem)]" data-is-streaming="false">
<div class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8">
<div>
<div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown">
