<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ai-statistic-2026-spending-adoption-and-sentiment/" data-wpel-link="internal">AI Statistic 2026: Spending, Adoption and Sentiment</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Dramatic market regime shift reshaping the global economy this year. Driven by a massive infrastructure race, tech giants have scaled their capex exponentially to historic highs, mirroring a widespread corporate surge where general AI adoption has broken out to unprecedented levels. Yet, while organizations aggressively scale their generative AI capabilities, a stark contrast remains between rapid enterprise implementation and cautious public sentiment. This comprehensive breakdown analyzes the hard data behind the billions spent, the actual phases of business integration, and the evolving human perspective—balancing immense technological optimism against lingering structural concerns.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">AI Spending </span></h2>
<p><iframe style="width: 100%; height: 600px; border: none; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);" title="Big Tech Capital Expenditure" src="https://sofosmorphism.github.io/Capex_yoy.html"><span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span><span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span></iframe></p>
<ul>
<li data-path-to-node="0,0,0"><b data-path-to-node="0,0,0" data-index-in-node="0">Exponential Growth:</b> All four tech giants have scaled their capex massively, driven by the AI infrastructure race from 2024 to 2026.</li>
<li data-path-to-node="0,1,0">Amazon has consistently been the largest or among the top spenders, peaking at <strong>$200B</strong> in 2026.</li>
<li data-path-to-node="0,2,0">In 2026, capex for all companies reached historic highs, with Amazon ($200B), Google ($190B), and Microsoft ($190B) leading the surge.</li>
<li data-path-to-node="0,2,0">Meta nearly doubled its spending from 2025 ($70B) to 2026 ($135B).</li>
<li data-path-to-node="0,4,0">Google&#8217;s capex remained flat for years before more than 3x from 2024 ($53B) to 2026 ($190B).</li>
<li>Microsoft grew its spend more than 10x, rising from <strong>$14B</strong> in 2018 to <strong>$190B</strong> in 2026.</li>
<li data-path-to-node="0,0,0">The percentage of organizations using AI in at least one business function increased more than fourfold, rising from <strong>20%</strong> in 2017 to <strong>88%</strong> in 2025.</li>
<li data-path-to-node="0,1,0">Generative AI usage more than doubled in just two years, jumping from <strong>33%</strong> in 2023 to <strong>79%</strong> in 2025.</li>
<li data-path-to-node="0,2,0">As of 2025, <strong>62%</strong> of organizations using AI are still in the early stages of implementation, consisting of experimenting (32%) and piloting (30%).</li>
<li data-path-to-node="0,3,0">Only <strong>7%</strong> of organizations using AI in 2025 have fully deployed and integrated the technology across the entire enterprise.</li>
<li data-path-to-node="0,4,0">General AI adoption remained mostly stagnant between 2019 (58%) and 2023 (55%) before experiencing an exponential upward breakout.</li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">AI Adoption </span></h2>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-203134" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Group-3832-1.png" alt="Top 10 countries by token volume" width="1974" height="1224" /></p>
<ul>
<li>The United States holds a commanding lead, accounting for <strong>47.17%</strong> of total global LLM token volume—nearly half of the market.</li>
<li>Following the US, the next tier—consisting of Singapore (9.21%), Germany (7.51%), and China (6.01%)—represents a substantial drop in market share, despite being the next largest contributors.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Globally, roughly </span><b>one in six</b> <span style="font-weight: 400;">people were using </span><b>generative</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> AI tools by the end of 2025.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>35.49%</strong> of people now use AI tools every day</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Only </span><b>8.5%</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> of people believe they can &#8220;always trust&#8221; AI Overviews when searching online</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>57%</strong> foresee AI increasing web traffic for their company.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>90%</strong> of tech workers are using AI tools</span></li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-203125 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Primary_usecases.png" alt="Primary AI Use Cases " width="2399" height="1411" /></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The top ways consumers use AI are as follows:</span>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Respond to people via text/email: <strong>45%</strong></span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Answer financial questions: <strong>43%</strong></span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Plan travel itinerary: <strong>38%</strong></span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Craft an email: <strong>31%</strong></span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Prepare for a job interview:<strong> 30%</strong></span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Write a social media post: <strong>25%</strong></span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Summarize complex or long copy: <strong>19%</strong></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">9 in 10 students want to learn more about AI in school.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">More than half (54%) could tell the difference between human and AI-generated content in early 2025,</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">About 2 out of 3 (67%) people would use ChatGPT instead of Google.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">ChatGPT once held the record for the fastest-growing consumer app, reaching 100 million users in about two months. However, DeepSeek broke that record in early 2025, surpassing 100 million users in just 20 days after the launch of the DeepSeek-R1 app.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cooking and meal planning is the top &#8220;life situation&#8221; AI use case</span></li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-203127" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Public-Perception-of-AI-in-Healthcare-1.png" alt="Public Perception of AI in Healthcare" width="2399" height="1387" /></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>38%</strong> also believed AI could help improve healthcare outcomes.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>40%</strong> also thought AI would reduce errors. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>51%</strong> thought AI would reduce instances of racial and ethnic bias.</span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">77% of devices being used now have some form of AI.</span></li>
</ul>
<h3>Enterprise</h3>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-203124" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Group-3829-1.png" alt="" width="2161" height="1411" /></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>88%</strong> of companies are now using AI in at least one business function, and <strong>83%</strong> of companies claim that AI is a top priority in their business plans. </span></li>
<li>The percentage of organizations using AI in at least one business function increased more than <strong>4x</strong>, rising from <strong>20%</strong> in 2017 to <strong>88%</strong> in 2025.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>9 out of 10</strong> organizations support AI for a competitive advantage.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In 2017, only <strong>20%</strong> of companies incorporated AI into their product offerings and business operations, in 2026, its <strong>88%</strong>, more than <strong>4x</strong> </span></li>
</ul>
<div id="attachment_203128" style="width: 1928px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203128" class="size-full wp-image-203128" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/AI-Adoption-Stages.png" alt="AI Adoption Stages" width="1918" height="1115" /><p id="caption-attachment-203128" class="wp-caption-text">AI Adoption Stages</p></div>
<ul>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="0,3,0"><strong>Only 7%</strong> of organizations using AI in 2025 have fully deployed and integrated the technology across the entire enterprise.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="0,4,0">General AI adoption remained mostly stagnant between 2019 (58%) and 2023 (55%) before experiencing an exponential upward breakout.</p>
</li>
<li>As of 2025, <strong>62%</strong> of organizations using AI are still in the early stages of implementation, consisting of experimenting (32%) and piloting (30%).</li>
<li>Generative AI usage more than doubled in just two years, jumping from <strong>33%</strong> in 2023 to <strong>79%</strong> in 2025.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">According to Forbes, the most common uses for AI in business are:</span>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Customer service – <strong>56%</strong></span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cybersecurity</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and fraud management – <strong>51%</strong></span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Digital personal assistants –<strong> 47%</strong></span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Customer relationship management – <strong>46%</strong></span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Inventory management – <strong>40%</strong></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Software development, marketing, and customer service are three fields that have seen the highest rate of adoption and investment.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-203129" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Barriers-to-AI-Adoption.png" alt="Barriers to AI Adoption" width="2143" height="1396" /></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The most common reason for businesses not using AI was <strong>finance/cost (51%).</strong></span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>43%</strong> of businesses are concerned about technology dependence.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>35%</strong> worry that they don’t have the technical skills to use AI.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>80%</strong> are concerned about AI being used for cyber attacks,</span>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>78%</strong> are concerned about AI being used for identity theft.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>74%</strong> are concerned about AI being used to create deceptive political ads.</span></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>63%</strong> of top-performing companies are increasing cloud budgets in order to to leverage GenAI.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">AI is used in drug development to discover new treatments.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Artificial intelligence effectively solved the 50-year-old biological mystery of protein folding and now being used to doing the research.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><b>Sentiment</b></h2>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>53%</strong> expect AI to streamline job processes within their organization.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Nearly <strong>25%</strong> of business owners worry about AI negatively affecting website traffic.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Nearly 2/3</strong> of business owners think AI will improve their customer relationships.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>97%</strong> of business owners think using ChatGPT will help their business.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Nearly 3/4</strong> (74%) of business owners expect AI to generate responses to customers, such as chatbots.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>7 in 10</strong> (70%) anticipate AI to speed up content generation processes.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>58%</strong> believe AI will be able to create personalized experiences for customers.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>50%</strong> of consumers view AI optimistically.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>54%</strong> of consumers think AI could improve the customer experience.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>65%</strong> of consumers trust businesses that use AI.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>14%</strong> of consumers do not trust businesses that use AI.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>21%</strong> of consumers are neutral on businesses using AI.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>78%</strong> of people polled think the benefits of generative AI outweigh the risks.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Another <strong>53%</strong> believe AI will be able to summarize information effectively.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Half of business owners expect AI to improve decision-making processes.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>47%</strong> anticipate AI improving their business credibility.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The same percentage, <strong>47%,</strong> believe AI will be able to translate information efficiently.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>52%</strong> of experts believe automation will displace jobs and also create new ones.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">AI could increase labor productivity growth by <strong>1.5 percentage points</strong> over the next ten years.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Globally, AI-driven growth could be nearly <strong>25%</strong> higher than automation without AI.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>46%</strong> of business owners expect AI to generate responses to colleagues, such as emails.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>44%</strong> anticipate AI being able to create content in different languages.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>41%</strong> foresee AI being used to fix coding errors effectively.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Nearly 1 in 3</strong> (30%) business owners expect AI to generate website copy for their company.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>51%</strong> of email marketers believe AI-supported email marketing is more effective than manual efforts</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>39%</strong> of respondents believe current AI technology is safe and secure.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>51%</strong> of men and <strong>40%</strong> of women say they’re more excited than concerned about AI.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>54%</strong> of consumers think that written content will improve with AI technology </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>4.1%</strong> of people surveyed think AI will have no benefits.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>12.4%</strong> believe AI will not have any potential drawbacks.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>51%</strong> think the problem of bias and unfair treatment would get better if AI was used more to do things like diagnose disease and recommend treatments for patients.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>67%</strong> of Americans say they would not want AI-based pain management systems to guiding their pain management treatment</span></li>
</ul>
